Interface Mogram

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Arg, Exerter, Identifiable, Request, Scopable, java.io.Serializable, Service, Substitutable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Context<T>, Domain, Exertion, Model, Modeling, StrategyContext
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AltMogram, ArrayContext, Block, CompoundExertion, ConditionalMogram, ContextResult, ControlContext, CustomContext, DataContext, EvaluationTask, Job, ListContext, LoopMogram, MapContext, ModelerNetTask, ModelerObjectTask, ModelTask, MultiFiMogram, NetBlock, NetJob, NetTask, ObjectBlock, ObjectJob, ObjectTask, OptMogram, PositionalContext, ProcModel, ProviderSession, ScopeContext, ServiceContext, ServiceExertion, ServiceMogram, SharedAssociativeContext, SharedIndexedContext, SignedServiceTask, SrvModel, Task

    public interface Mogram
extends Identifiable, Exerter, Scopable, Substitutable, Request
    An top-level common interface for all mograms in SORCER.
    Author:
    Mike Sobolewski

    • Method Detail

      • exert

        <T extends Mogram> T exert(Transaction txn,
                           Arg... entries)
                    throws TransactionException,
                           MogramException,
                           java.rmi.RemoteException
        Exerts this mogram by the assigned service provider if it is set. If a service provider is not set then at runtime it bounds to any available provider that matches this mogram's signature of the PROCESS fiType. Service exertions and models are instances of mograms.
        Parameters:
        txn - The transaction (if any) under which to exert.
        Returns:
        a resulting exertion
        Throws:
        net.jini.core.transaction.TransactionException - if a transaction error occurs
        ExertionException - if processing this exertion causes an error
        TransactionException
        MogramException
        java.rmi.RemoteException

      • selectFidelity

        ServiceFidelity selectFidelity(java.lang.String selection)
        Returns a service fidelity of this exertion that consists of process signature, all pre-processing, post-processing, and append signatures. There is only one process signature defining late binding to the service provider processing this exertion.
        Parameters:
        selection - The service fidelity name.
        Returns:
        a service fidelity

        ServiceFidelity<Signature> getSelectedFidelity()
        Returns a service fidelity of this exertion that consists of process signature, all pre-processing, post-processing, and append signatures. There is only one process signature defining late binding to the service provider processing this exertion.
        Returns:
        a collection of all service signatures
